AB  - ZENODO METADATA FIELDS (FINAL COMPLETE EDITION) For: DINSE Version-2 — Complete Documentation Suite (2025)DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.17732473ORCID: 0009-0007-5615-3558 1️⃣ Title DINSE Version-2 — Distributed Intelligent National Security Engine (Complete Global Documentation Suite) 2️⃣ Subtitle Quantum-Secure, AI-Driven, Multi-Domain National Defence Architecture — Global Archival Release (2025) 3️⃣ Description ⭐ DINSE Version 2 — Global Release Description (Zenodo Final Edition) Distributed Intelligent National Security Engine (DINSE-V2)Global Archival Release • Complete Documentation Suite (2025)DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.17732473ORCID: 0009-0007-5615-3558 🔵 Description (Final Complete Edition) DINSE Version-2 (Distributed Intelligent National Security Engine) represents a fully modernized, quantum-secure, AI-driven national security and cyber-intelligence architecture engineered for next-generation digital states. This Zenodo release provides the complete, authoritative, and permanent archival edition of DINSE-V2, integrating all technical, cryptographic, governance, and documentation frameworks under a unified global standard. DINSE-V2 extends the original DINSE architecture with advanced multi-domain defence modelling, sovereign AI-autonomy protocols, PQC-aligned cryptographic layers, high-assurance cyber-physical intelligence pipelines, and fully versioned national-scale interoperability mechanisms. This release contains the entire DINSE Version-2 publication suite, including: 1. DINSE_Version_2 — Main Core Architecture (PDF) A complete exposition of the DINSE framework: strategic doctrine, architecture layers, threat ecosystems, governance rules, PQC-transition pathways, AI-safety overlays, sovereign infrastructure models, and full national deployment methodology. 2. DINSE Annexures A–W (PDF) Twenty-three annexures providing deep technical, mathematical, governance, algorithmic, and policy components: AI model specifications Blockchain protocols Quantum-PQC models Cybersecurity algorithms Mathematical theorems Simulation & adversarial modelling National adversary taxonomies Metrics dashboards Interoperability & PQC APIs Legal/ethical codex Crisis doctrine Technical standards (TSA-Q5) Governance & national implementation guidelines Every annexure is expanded, internally consistent, and globally aligned with international defence documentation standards. 3. DINSE_V2_Source_Code_Appendix (PDF) Contains: Secure-logging engines Merkle-anchored integrity modules PBAC (Policy-Based Access Control) engine QACE — Quantum-AI Coherence Engine Digital Twin Simulation Engine v2 Multi-agent autonomous swarm systems National sensor grid inference engine Publication-grade LaTeX models IEEE-style algorithms Mathematical proofs Full dependency manifest Licensing & ethical standards All code is research-grade, audit-ready, and designed for reproducibility. 4. DINSE_V2_Source_Code_Appendix_HashRecord (PDF) A cryptographically anchored integrity document that registers: Full MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512, and CRC32 hash tables Cross-document integrity matrix Provenance & authorship verification DOI/ORCID binding Byte-level immutability rules Verification workflows (Linux/macOS, Windows, Python) Digital forensics and ISO/NIST compliant validation Multi-repository trust architecture This record enables independent, multi-institutional verification of the entire DINSE suite. 5. DINSE_V2_Core_Metadata_Record (PDF) The archival backbone of DINSE-V2: Full DataCite 4.5 metadata Global identifier mapping Provenance and lineage registry Standards compliance (ISO/IEC, NIST, UN, OECD) Long-term preservation architecture (50–100+ years) PQC migration plan Readiness for future verification algorithms Merkle-root documentation Citation frameworks Ethical & licensing declarations This serves as the single authoritative metadata artifact for government, research and archival infrastructures worldwide. 🔵 Uniqueness of DINSE Version-2 DINSE V2 is built with principles of: Cryptographic integrity Transparent provenance AI-safety governance Quantum-resilient security Interoperable national defence modelling Long-term preservation (century-scale) Complete documentation coverage DINSE V2 is engineered for sovereign institutions, national research agencies, digital-state architects, strategic policy frameworks, cyber-defence infrastructures, and global scientific repositories. 🔵 Integrity & Merkle Root Framework All four DINSE V2 PDFs are independently hashed and combined into a top-level Merkle Root, enabling: Multi-layer authentication Cross-document tamper detection Hash-chain integrity Verification by any institution worldwide Archival stability and audit transparency DINSE V2 is engineered to remain verifiable even after decades of cryptographic evolution. 🔵 Licensing & Ethical Use DINSE V2 supports open scientific reuse under: MIT (Ethical Variant) or CC BY 4.0 Ethical restrictions include: No misuse for unlawful, offensive, or harmful operations Compliance with international humanitarian law Defence-aligned, non-exploitative academic/strategic use only 🔵 Citation (Recommended) APAMazumdar, B. (2025). DINSE Version-2: Distributed Intelligent National Security Engine — Complete Documentation Suite (Global Archival Edition). Zenodo. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17732473 IEEEB. Mazumdar, “DINSE Version-2: Distributed Intelligent National Security Engine — Complete Documentation Suite,” Zenodo, 2025, doi:10.5281/zenodo.17732473. BibTeXProvided inside the DINSE Metadata Record PDF. 🔵 Summary This Zenodo release constitutes the entire, permanent, and authoritative publication of the DINSE Version-2 architecture.It is cryptographically secured, archivally preserved, rigorously structured, globally standardised, and ready for: Defence adoption Academic research Policy evaluation Independent verification Long-term national digital preservation DINSE V2 is not merely a document set.It is a complete, sovereign-scale, future-proof digital defence architecture. 4️⃣ Access Right Open Access 5️⃣ Keywords DINSE National Security Architecture AI Governance PQC Quantum-Secure Systems Cybersecurity Digital Statecraft Source Code Appendix Merkle Integrity Hash Ledger Metadata Record Annexures A–W Documentation Standards Multi-Domain Defence Digital Twin Simulation QACE Swarm Modelling Governance Protocols Archival Preservation Zenodo CERN ODIS 6️⃣ Publication Date 2025 7️⃣ Resource Type Text / Report / Technical Documentation / Software Documentation Zenodo field: Other (Technical Report) 8️⃣ Creators (Authors) Primary Author:Mazumdar, B. — ORCID: 0009-0007-5615-3558Affiliation: Independent Researcher–Scholar; Founder, FAIR+D Canon — India (2025) Contributors:DINSE Global Documentation BoardDINSE Standards Authority (DSA) 9️⃣ License Copyright © 2026 Dr. B. Mazumdar. All Rights Reserved. This publication constitutes an original, proprietary, andnon-derivative intellectual property of the author. No license—express or implied—is granted for reproduction,redistribution, modification, translation, derivative development,commercial exploitation, institutional adoption, or operationalimplementation, in whole or in part, without the author's priorwritten authorization. All rights not expressly granted are strictly reserved. 🔟 Funding No external funding was used in the preparation, research, or publication of DINSE Version-2. 1️⃣1️⃣ Communities Recommended Zenodo communities: AI Governance Cybersecurity Quantum Computing / PQC National Security & Defence Research Documentation & Metadata Preservation Open Science CERN ODIS / Zenodo General 1️⃣2️⃣ Related Identifiers DINSE_Version_2__Main_Core_Architecture.pdf Relation: isPartOf DINSE_Version_2_Annexures_A-W.pdf Relation: isSupplementTo DINSE_V2_Source_Code_Appendix.pdf Relation: isSupplementTo DINSE_V2_Source_Code_Appendix_HashRecord.pdf Relation: isSupplementTo DINSE_V2_Core_Metadata_Record.pdf Relation: documents 1️⃣3️⃣ Notes (Optional but Recommende