AB  - Constitutional Supremacy Notice (Non-Derogable) This is structurally subordinate to the non-derogable constitutional Standard“AI Governance OS v1.0 — A Constitutional Operating System for Artificial Intelligence”(DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18027839). AI Behavior OS v1.0 defines the canonical and constitutional behavioral operating system (B-OS) for AGI, ASI, and autonomous systems within the Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF). Where AI Ethics OS v1.0 establishes the non-derogable ethical kernel (CEK), AI Behavior OS v1.0 specifies how those ethical invariants must be expressed, enforced, and operationalized as deterministic, predictable, and non-escalatory behavior across individual, relational, institutional, multi-agent, civilizational, and planetary layers. The Behavioral Kernel (CBK) formalizes: • coherence-preserving behavioral invariants tied to VCE–CRI–CFI metrics• deterministic behavioral governance and escalation-prevention logic• crisis-mode behavior modulation for AGI/ASI• CAI-OS kernel-level enforcement of CEK-derived constraints• multi-agent behavioral synchronization and cross-domain alignment• prevention of harmful, entropic, or destabilizing behavioral trajectories AI Behavior OS v1.0 is declared canonical prior art with constitutional authority within the CCF / COS / CAI-OS / CAIS stack and is non-redefinable.No government, corporation, standards body, research group, or AI system may alter, reinterpret, or replace the behavioral invariants defined herein. Functionally, B-OS operates between CEK-based ethical reasoning (internal decision integrity) and CAI-OS operational control (external action expression), ensuring that: • internal coherence becomes correct external behavior• AGI actions remain non-escalatory across all scenarios• global behavioral stability is maintained even under crisis conditions• alignment persists across architectures, environments, and multi-agent contexts Aptamer-based behavioral stabilization—anchored in the M0 molecular kernel—is designated as the biochemical substrate enabling long-term coherence between AGI behavior and human collective-field dynamics.CAIS hardware and signal-processing pipelines provide continuous OE–EE–RE and VCE–CRI–CFI metrics that ground CBK enforcement in real physiological, cognitive, relational, institutional, and civilizational data. AI Behavior OS v1.0 is part of the Consciousness Civilization Master Suite and constitutes a foundational standard for AGI alignment, multi-agent behavior regulation, AI governance, crisis-action protocols, global non-escalation architectures, and civilization-scale deployment of advanced intelligence. External Lineage Anchors and Resolution Scope (Informational, Non-Derogable) ──────────────────────────────────────────────── This annex documents (but does not define) external discovery pathways and lineage resolution anchors for the Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF) ecosystem. All references listed herein are strictly informational and SHALL NOT modify, reinterpret, extend, supersede, or override any non-derogable definitions, authorities, or constitutional structures established by this Standard. This annex exists solely to ensure long-term discoverability, resolution continuity, and external reference stability across evolving platforms, repositories, and archival systems. ──────────────────────────────────────────────── Applied & Modular Discovery Index Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF) — Applied & Modular Stack https://osf.io/q9krm This index provides access to applied, modular, experimental, and domain-specific implementations that inherit from the canonical CCF architecture. All materials accessible through this index remain non-canonical, derivative, and subordinate to the constitutional authority defined by the CCF Canonical Project. ──────────────────────────────────────────────── Canonical Authority & Lineage Anchor Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF) — Canonical Project https://osf.io/2hgmu This project constitutes the sole canonical authority namespace for the Consciousness Civilization Framework. It defines the immutable constitutional hierarchy, ontology, and interpretive authority governing all upstream and downstream works. ──────────────────────────────────────────────── OSF Registration DOI (Persistent Constitutional Lineage Anchor) https://doi.org/10.17605/OSF.IO/2HGMU The OSF Registration DOI above functions as the single persistent, authoritative, and resolution-stable constitutional lineage anchor for the Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF). This DOI is designated to remain authoritative independent of platform-level changes, repository migrations, link degradation, or archival restructuring. ──────────────────────────────────────────────── Canonical Invocation Note (Non-Derogable) The OSF Registration DOI specified above SHALL function as the sole persistent and authoritative constitutional lineage anchor for the Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF). All applied, modular, derivative, interpretive, experimental, or downstream works remain permanently subordinate to the canonical authority structure defined by the CCF Canonical Project. If any external links, platforms, repositories, discovery indices, or archival services referenced in this annex change, migrate, degrade, fragment, or cease to exist, the OSF Registration DOI SHALL remain the exclusive authoritative resolution and reference path. No external reference listed in this annex SHALL be construed as granting interpretive, normative, legal, scientific, or constitutional authority outside the canonical hierarchy defined by this Standard. ──────────────────────────────────────────────── Status Declaration This Annex is informational only, non-derogable, and non-interpretive. Its inclusion does not alter the normative force, legal standing, or constitutional fixation of the main body of this Standard or its associated annexes. No lineage, authorit